               <p>CHARLES CHURCH. I am clerk to Robert Simpson, who is a <rs id="t18171029-42-viclabel220" type="occupation">wholesale linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18171029-42-victim311 t18171029-42-viclabel220"></join>, and lives in Watling-street. On the 6th of October, about six o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came into the warehouse, and took the piece of linen off the counter; I was at the end of the warehouse - I turned round, followed her, and stopped her with it before she got out. She pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in distress.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18171029-42-verdict221" type="verdictDescription">
